Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Candente, Credicorp, Intergroup

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-10-07T17:34:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-07/peru-stocks-buenaventura-candente-credicorp-intergroup.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 2:29 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index was little changed at 17,757.46. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index was little changed at 2,308.53.  Banking shares rebounded as investors bet companies will
post strong third-quarter earnings, said Arlen Lahura, a trader
at Lima-based brokerage Coril SAB.  Intergroup Financial Services Corp. (IFS)  , the owner of
Peru’s fourth-largest bank, Interbank, rose 2.5 percent to $23.
 Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services
holding company, gained 1.3 percent to $93.  Banco Continental SA (CONTINC1) 
(CONTINC1 PE), the local unit of  Spain ’s Banco Bilbao Vizcaya
Argentaria SA, climbed 1 percent to 5.15 soles.  Miners gained after metals advanced in New York and  London .  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration
company, rose for a third session, adding 2 percent to $1.01.
Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s biggest
precious-metals miner, advanced 1.8 percent to $40.20.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1) 
(MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin producer, rose 1.2
percent to 2.45 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  